HEADWORD: Reimbursable
<hw>Re`im*burs"a*ble</hw> <pr>(r?`?m*b?rs"?*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[CF. F. <ets>remboursable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being
repaid; repayable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A loan has been made of two millions of dollars,
<qex>reimbursable</qex> in ten years.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reimburse</ent>⟦br⟧
